<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881017-0140 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News: USX Unit Promotes McVay </HL><SO> </SO><CO> X WNEWS </CO><DATELINE> PITTSBURGH  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Texas Oil andamp; Gas Corp., a unit of USX Corp., said Leland J. McVay has been promoted to president of its TXO Production Corp. subsidiary, effective Nov. 1.    Mr. McVay, executive vice president since April of the exploration and production unit, will succeed A.D. Carter Jr., who is resigning to pursue personal business interests. Mr. McVay joined Texas Oil andamp; Gas in 1980 after working 10 years for Conoco Inc.    Texas Oil andamp; Gas gathers, transports and processes natural gas and also explores for and produces gas, crude oil and condensate. </TEXT></DOC>